<TITLE> Two drown in Dhaka boat capsize </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 29 (bdnews24.com)Two people, including a young boy, drowned as their boat capsized in a beel, an open water body, near the Turag river in the capital on Wednesday, police said. The dead were identified as 12-year old Ronnie, who was plying the small country boat, and a passenger, local madrasah teacher Abdul Aziz, aged 50. Turag police chief, Khandaker Rezaul Hasan, told bdnews24.com that the boat, with three people aboard, overturned just after noon in the beel at Shekhdir Tek behind the Uttaran Housing Project. "Two people including Abdul Aziz got into Ronnie's boat to go to Shekhdir Tek," Hasan said. "While returning, the boat sank in the middle of the beel and all three went in the water. One managed to swim ashore but Ronnie and Aziz drowned." Toufiqul Islam, of the Dhaka fire service control room, told bdnews24.com that a team of divers reached the spot at 12:45pm and retrieved two dead bodies at around 2:45pm. bd
